-- Oppenheimer Funds' Leverenz Tops Emerging Fund List for the Sixth Time
-- B y   A n n a - L o u i s e   J a c k s o n
-- 2010-10-25T04:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/oppenheimerfunds-leverenz-tops-emerging-funds-list-for-6th-time.html
The  Oppenheimer Developing Markets 
Fund outperformed other emerging-economy mutual funds in
Bloomberg Rankings’ evaluation of long- and short-term returns
for the sixth straight month.  The OppenheimerFunds Inc. investment pool, managed by
 Justin Leverenz , returned 27.2 percent in the 12 months ended
Sept. 30 and an annualized 15.2 percent over five years,
according to Bloomberg data.  The best one-year return among six categories in the
ranking was the  Target Maturities Trust Series 2025  Fund’s 34.3
percent. That portfolio topped the U.S. bond category, returning
an annualized 11.8 percent over five years and 19.6 percent over
three years. It’s managed by American Century Investment
Services Inc.’s  Dave MacEwen ,  Robert Gahagan ,  Brian Howell  and
 James Platz .  A summary of the best-scoring fund in each category is
below, with links to total-return data. For the complete
ranking, which evaluates U.S.-based funds with assets greater
than $250 million based on one-, three- and five-year total
returns and an adjustment for risk, click here.  To contact the reporter on this story:
